<!DOCTYPE html>
<h1 id="name">Brad Clark</h1>
<h3 id="title">Chief Operations Officer</h3>
<div id="bio">
<h3>Chief Operations Officer</h3>
	<div id="preview">
		<p>Brad Clark has more than 20 years of experience in business administration and software design &amp; development.</p>
		<p>He leads the operations team responsible for deploying Mindshare&rsquo;s state-of-the-art customer feedback systems.</p>
	</div>
	<p>Brad&rsquo;s experience covers the design, development, and deployment of enterprise-wide software systems. These include financial planning sales systems, web collaboration tools, and voice of the customer management solutions.</p>
	<p>The operations team takes pride in delivering solutions that turn customer feedback into actionable direction for Mindshare&rsquo;s clients. He is also involved in product strategy and growing the company. He loves staying connected with Mindshare&rsquo;s customers whenever possible. </p>
	<p>Brad started his career as the accounting manager at Sterling Wentworth Corporation. After the company was acquired by Sungard Data Systems, he became senior project manager, overseeing the implementation of Sungard&rsquo;s financial sales and analysis systems with clients such as IBM, Prudential Securities, and AXA Advisors. After Sungard, Brad moved on to become Director of Program Management at BlueStep, Inc., where he was responsible for the design and development of the company&rsquo;s web collaboration product.</p>
	<p>In 2002, Brad came to Mindshare. His experience in accounting, software development, and project management has made him versatile and vital to Mindshare&rsquo;s growth. He&rsquo;s at his best when teaching clients how to grow their business by listening to the voices of their customers&mdash;one customer at a time.</p>
	<p>Possessing a passion for ice cream and the customer, Brad relates to the words of Ben Cohen, Co-Founder of Ben &amp; Jerry&rsquo;s: &ldquo;There is a spiritual aspect to our lives&mdash;when we give we receive, when a business does something good for somebody, that somebody feels good about them!&rdquo; There are great customer experiences happening every day in business. The opportunity to find and share these real customer experiences brings Brad back to work every day. </p>
	<p>He loves to vacation with his wonderful wife and four beautiful daughters. His favorite hobby is anything that allows him to spend time with them. </p>
	<p>Brad has a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business finance from Brigham Young University.</p>
</div>